HEADWORD: Puit
<hw>Puit</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>puits</ets>,
from L. <ets>puteus</ets> well.]</ety> <def>A well; a small stream; a
fountain; a spring.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>puits</qex> flowing from the fountain of life.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puke</ent>⟦br⟧
